{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Last year at TED we aimed to try to clarify"},{"time":4000,"text":"the overwhelming complexity"},{"time":6000,"text":"and richness that we experience at the conference"},{"time":9000,"text":"in a project called Big Viz."},{"time":11000,"text":"And the Big Viz is a collection of 650 sketches"},{"time":14000,"text":"that were made by two visual artists."},{"time":16000,"text":"David Sibbet from The Grove,"},{"time":18000,"text":"and Kevin Richards, from Autodesk,"},{"time":20000,"text":"made 650 sketches that strive to capture"},{"time":23000,"text":"the essence of each presenter's ideas."},{"time":27000,"text":"And the consensus was: it really worked."},{"time":29000,"text":"These sketches brought to life the key ideas,"},{"time":33000,"text":"the portraits, the magic moments"},{"time":35000,"text":"that we all experienced last year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37000,"text":"This year we were thinking, \"Why does it work?\""},{"time":40000,"text":"What is it about animation,"},{"time":42000,"text":"graphics, illustrations, that create meaning?"},{"time":45000,"text":"And this is an important question to ask and answer"},{"time":48000,"text":"because the more we understand how the brain creates meaning,"},{"time":51000,"text":"the better we can communicate,"},{"time":53000,"text":"and, I also think, the better we can think and collaborate together."},{"time":56000,"text":"So this year we're going to visualize how"},{"time":58000,"text":"the brain visualizes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60000,"text":"Cognitive psychologists now tell us that the brain"},{"time":62000,"text":"doesn't actually see the world as it is,"},{"time":65000,"text":"but instead, creates a series of mental models"},{"time":68000,"text":"through a collection of \"Ah-ha moments,\""},{"time":70000,"text":"or moments of discovery, through various processes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72000,"text":"The processing, of course, begins with the eyes."},{"time":75000,"text":"Light enters, hits the back of the retina, and is circulated,"},{"time":78000,"text":"most of which is streamed to the very back of the brain,"},{"time":81000,"text":"at the primary visual cortex."},{"time":83000,"text":"And primary visual cortex sees just simple geometry,"},{"time":86000,"text":"just the simplest of shapes."},{"time":88000,"text":"But it also acts like a kind of relay station"},{"time":91000,"text":"that re-radiates and redirects information"},{"time":93000,"text":"to many other parts of the brain."},{"time":96000,"text":"As many as 30 other parts that selectively make more sense,"},{"time":99000,"text":"create more meaning through the kind of \"Ah-ha\" experiences."},{"time":102000,"text":"We're only going to talk about three of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104000,"text":"So the first one is called the ventral stream."},{"time":107000,"text":"It's on this side of the brain."},{"time":109000,"text":"And this is the part of the brain that will recognize what something is."},{"time":113000,"text":"It's the \"what\" detector."},{"time":115000,"text":"Look at a hand. Look at a remote control. Chair. Book."},{"time":119000,"text":"So that's the part of the brain that is activated"},{"time":122000,"text":"when you give a word to something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124000,"text":"A second part of the brain is called the dorsal stream."},{"time":127000,"text":"And what it does is locates the object"},{"time":130000,"text":"in physical body space."},{"time":133000,"text":"So if you look around the stage here"},{"time":135000,"text":"you'll create a kind of mental map of the stage."},{"time":138000,"text":"And if you closed your eyes you'd be able to mentally navigate it."},{"time":141000,"text":"You'd be activating the dorsal stream if you did that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144000,"text":"The third part that I'd like to talk about"},{"time":146000,"text":"is the limbic system."},{"time":148000,"text":"And this is deep inside of the brain. It's very old, evolutionarily."},{"time":151000,"text":"And it's the part that feels."},{"time":153000,"text":"It's the kind of gut center, where you see an image"},{"time":155000,"text":"and you go, \"Oh! I have a strong"},{"time":157000,"text":"or emotional reaction to whatever I'm seeing.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":161000,"text":"So the combination of these processing centers"},{"time":164000,"text":"help us make meaning in very different ways."},{"time":168000,"text":"So what can we learn about this? How can we apply this insight?"},{"time":171000,"text":"Well, again, the schematic view"},{"time":173000,"text":"is that the eye visually interrogates what we look at."},{"time":176000,"text":"The brain processes this in parallel, the figments of information"},{"time":179000,"text":"asking a whole bunch of questions"},{"time":181000,"text":"to create a unified mental model."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183000,"text":"So, for example, when you look at this image"},{"time":186000,"text":"a good graphic invites the eye to dart around,"},{"time":189000,"text":"to selectively create a visual logic."},{"time":191000,"text":"So the act of engaging, and looking at the image creates the meaning."},{"time":196000,"text":"It's the selective logic."},{"time":198000,"text":"Now we've augmented this and spatialized this information."},{"time":201000,"text":"Many of you may remember the magic wall that we built"},{"time":204000,"text":"in conjunction with Perceptive Pixel"},{"time":206000,"text":"where we quite literally create an infinite wall."},{"time":209000,"text":"And so we can compare and contrast the big ideas."},{"time":211000,"text":"So the act of engaging and creating interactive imagery"},{"time":214000,"text":"enriches meaning."},{"time":216000,"text":"It activates a different part of the brain."},{"time":219000,"text":"And then the limbic system"},{"time":221000,"text":"is activated when we see motion, when we see color,"},{"time":224000,"text":"and there are primary shapes and pattern detectors"},{"time":227000,"text":"that we've heard about before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229000,"text":"So the point of this is what?"},{"time":231000,"text":"We make meaning by seeing,"},{"time":234000,"text":"by an act of visual interrogation."},{"time":236000,"text":"The lessons for us are three-fold."},{"time":238000,"text":"First, use images to clarify what we're trying to communicate."},{"time":242000,"text":"Secondly make those images interactive"},{"time":245000,"text":"so that we engage much more fully."},{"time":247000,"text":"And the third is to augment memory"},{"time":249000,"text":"by creating a visual persistence."},{"time":251000,"text":"These are techniques that can be used to be --"},{"time":254000,"text":"that can be applied in a wide range of problem solving."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258000,"text":"So the low-tech version looks like this."},{"time":260000,"text":"And, by the way, this is the way in which"},{"time":262000,"text":"we develop and formulate"},{"time":264000,"text":"strategy within Autodesk,"},{"time":266000,"text":"in some of our organizations and some of our divisions."},{"time":269000,"text":"What we literally do is have the teams"},{"time":271000,"text":"draw out the entire strategic plan"},{"time":274000,"text":"on one giant wall."},{"time":276000,"text":"And it's very powerful because everyone gets to see everything else."},{"time":280000,"text":"There's always a room, always a place"},{"time":282000,"text":"to be able to make sense of all of the components"},{"time":285000,"text":"in the strategic plan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287000,"text":"This is a time-lapse view of it."},{"time":290000,"text":"You can ask the question, \"Who's the boss?\""},{"time":292000,"text":"You'll be able to figure that out. (Laughter)"},{"time":300000,"text":"So the act of collectively and collaboratively"},{"time":303000,"text":"building the image"},{"time":305000,"text":"transforms the collaboration."},{"time":308000,"text":"No Powerpoint is used in two days."},{"time":310000,"text":"But instead the entire team"},{"time":312000,"text":"creates a shared mental model"},{"time":314000,"text":"that they can all agree on and move forward on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317000,"text":"And this can be enhanced and augmented with"},{"time":319000,"text":"some emerging digital technology."},{"time":322000,"text":"And this is our great unveiling for today."},{"time":325000,"text":"And this is an emerging set of technologies"},{"time":327000,"text":"that use large-screen displays"},{"time":330000,"text":"with intelligent calculation in the background"},{"time":333000,"text":"to make the invisible visible."},{"time":335000,"text":"Here what we can do is look at sustainability, quite literally."},{"time":338000,"text":"So a team can actually look at"},{"time":341000,"text":"all the key components that heat the structure"},{"time":344000,"text":"and make choices and then see the end result"},{"time":346000,"text":"that is visualized on this screen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349000,"text":"So making images meaningful has three components."},{"time":352000,"text":"The first again, is making ideas clear by visualizing them."},{"time":355000,"text":"Secondly, making them interactive."},{"time":357000,"text":"And then thirdly, making them persistent."},{"time":359000,"text":"And I believe that these three principles"},{"time":361000,"text":"can be applied to solving some of the very tough problems"},{"time":365000,"text":"that we face in the world today. Thanks so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}